The paper deals with distributed agreement in dynamic networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the availability of communication links, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper introduces a new concept called vertex-stable root components (VSRCs), which is a topic that falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also presents a consensus algorithm, which is a topic that falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the feasibility of gracefully degrading consensus, which is a topic that falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
